description: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by allocating its assets using a moderately conservative investment style that seeks to maximize the benefits of diversification, which focuses on investing portions of its assets in underlying ETFs that invest primarily in equity securities, as well as in underlying ETFs that invest primarily in fixed-income securities. Specifically, the fund's target allocation is to invest approximately 25%-55% of its total assets in equity ETFs and approximately 45%-75% of its total assets in fixed income ETFs.
name: Invesco Moderately Conservative Multi-Asset Allocation ETF
